{"id": 223744736, "title": "Minor Derailment: NRC Assures Of Normal Train Operations Along Abuja-Kaduna Corridor", "text": "ABUJA \u2013 The management of the Nigerian Railway Corporation(NRC) has assured the passengers and the general public that the minor derailment of coach at Jeremy station will not disrupt operations of passenger train services between Kaduna-Rigasa, and Idu Abuja corridors. In a statement signed by Yakubu Mahmood, Deputy Director Public Relations, noted that all the passengers on board the Kaduna-Rigasa to Idu Abuja arrived their respective destinations safely. \u201cNRC hereby informs the general public especially our valued passengers that normal passenger train services between Kaduna-Rigasa, Idu Abuja continues despite minor derailment of our coach at Jeremy station this morning. \u201cAll the passengers on board the Kaduna-Rigasa to Idu Abuja arrived their respective destinations safely. \u201cMeanwhile, team of NRC Engineers are already at the site to restore the affected locations. \u201cNigerian Railway Corporation Management regrets any inconveniences to our affected valued passengers. \u201cNRC wishes to assure our valued passengers of our efforts towards ensuring their safety and comfort always\u201d .", "summary": "<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"><img width=\"216\" height=\"121\" src=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240526-WA0044.jpg\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" /></div>ABUJA &#8211; The management of the Nigerian Railway Corporation(NRC) has assured the passengers and the general public that the minor derailment of coach at Jeremy station will not disrupt operations of passenger train services between Kaduna-Rigasa, and Idu Abuja corridors. In a statement signed by Yakubu Mahmood, Deputy Director Public Relations, noted that all the [&#8230;]", "url": "https://independent.ng/minor-derailment-nrc-assures-of-normal-train-operations-along-abuja